  "title": "Early Interventionist @Woodlands",
  "description": "<p>The Early Interventionist is responsible for providing quality and effective learning experiences for students through the best deliverance of the curriculum and use of effective teaching and classroom management strategies.</p>\n<p>Key responsibilities include:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assess, plans and executes action curriculum</li>\n  <li>Prepare curriculum resources</li>\n  <li>To provide and maintain a safe, healthy and conducive learning environment for students</li>\n  <li>Maintain student records</li>\n  <li>Assess progress of learning and teaching programmes</li>\n  <li>Implement Individualised Education Plan (IEP)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>- Possess a diploma with a Diploma in Early Childhood Intervention (Special Needs) (ADECISN); or possess a relevant diploma in Specialist Diploma in Early Childhood Intervention/Certificate in Autism and Higher Certificate in Autism</p>\n<p>- Diploma in Early Childhood</p>",
